F

Feature - Class in FeatureExtractorLibrary
Feature is the class that contains the different feature values; besides the constructors and getters it has a generateHeader function and an overloaded toString method.
Feature(double[], String, int) - Constructor for class FeatureExtractorLibrary.Feature
This constructor gets all the data in an array and supposing that the order is correct fills the Feature attributes.
Feature(double[], double[], double[], double[], double[], int, double[], String) - Constructor for class FeatureExtractorLibrary.Feature
This constructor gets all the data in arrays grouped by the type of attribute to fill the Feature attributes.
Feature(double, double, double, double, double, double, double, double, double, double, double, double, double, double, double, double, double, double, double, double[], double[], double[], double[], String) - Constructor for class FeatureExtractorLibrary.Feature
This constructor gets all the data in separate parameters, one by one, until it reaches the histograms, which are passed through arrays; the number of bins is not needed, but the userID of the subject is needed to fill the Feature attributes.
FeatureExtractor - Class in FeatureExtractorLibrary
This is a class with static methods meant to extract features from a dataset given as an ArrayList of Accelerometer objects or a CSV file, using the settings from Setting class.
FeatureExtractorException - Exception in FeatureExtractorLibrary
FeatureExtractorException is a custom exception used in FeatureExtractorLibrary
FeatureExtractorLibrary - package FeatureExtractorLibrary
 
FeatureExtractorLibraryMainTest - Class in FeatureExtractorLibrary
FeatureExtractorLibraryMainTest is the class I used to test the FeatureExtractor class
FeatureExtractorLibraryMainTest() - Constructor for class FeatureExtractorLibrary.FeatureExtractorLibraryMainTest
